article.headline: Florida State wins its last home game of the season
article.linkText: No. 25 Seminoles need 3OT to beat Va. Tech
article.story:
TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (SportsTicker) -- Roneeka Hodges scored 23 points and Ganiyat Adeduntan added 20 and 14 rebounds as No. 25 Florida State needed three overtimes to post a 94-83 victory over Virginia Tech in an Atlantic Coast Conference contest.

Hodges was 9-of-25 from the field, including 1-of-8 from the arc, as Florida State (22-6, 8-5 ACC) shot 45 percent (33-of-74) in its final home game of the season.

Alicia Gladden scored 18 points, Holly Johnson added 16 and eight boards and Linnea Liljestrand chipped in 10 as five players reached double digits for the Seminoles, who have won eight in a row against the Hokies.

Dawn Chriss scored 33 points on 14-of-18 shooting and gathered nine rebounds for Virginia Tech (15-10, 4-8).

Britney Anderson scored 18 points, Carrie Mason added 13, Erin Gibson had 10 and 16 rebounds and Kerri Gardin grabbed 11 boards for the Hokies, who failed on seven 3-point attempts.
